\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals to perennials. Raceme ebracteate. Sepals erect; petals abruptly contracted into claw; filaments without appendages. Fruit a transversely articulate siliqua; lower segment very short, slender, seedless, indehiscent; upper circular in section, indehiscent, straight-sided, or lomentaceous (at least in part), or constricted between the seeds but not breaking up into 1-seeded portions; beak narrow, seedless.
\par

