\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. R. raphanistrum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 669 (1753) ({\i R. sylvestris} Lam.). Plant usually more or less hispid; stem 15-150 cm, erect, branched. Basal and lower cauline leaves lyrate; upper usually entire. Sepals 5-10 mm, elliptic-lanceolate, obtuse; petals about twice as long as the sepals, white, yellow, lilac or violet. Pedicels 1-5 cm in fruit. Siliqua erecto-patent. Seeds 1·5-4 mm, ovoid to subglobose, usually reticulate.{\i  Throughout Europe, but only as an alien in the extreme north.} All territories except Sb.
